The paper proposes a method for constructing a concise fuzzy system model using soft subspace clustering and sparse learning. This involves techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with modeling complex nonlinear systems, which could also place it in the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DM (Data Mining).
